OL,5, Both Andrew Malkinson and John McCarthy
OL,6, have been deprived of their liberty.   
OL,7, One spent 17 years in prison for a     
OL,8, crime he didn't commit, the other was  
OL,9, held hostage for more than five years. 
OL,11,FWhen he was invited to guest edit Radio
OL,12,F4's Today programme, Mr Malkinson asked
OL,13,Fto meet Mr McCarthy. Face-to-face they 
OL,14,Fdiscussed the "shock and surreality" of
OL,15,Fhaving been prisoners.                 
OL,17,FFrom the confines of his British prison
OL,18,Fcell, Andrew Malkinson would lose      
OL,19,Fhimself in astronomy books.            
